titlelocalization.rawText: The share prices of Vien Pascal, Pierre Zola Company and dozens of other companies had fallen by up to 30% at the end of trading on the New York Stock Exchange.

descriptionlocalization.rawText: In a single day, panicked investors sold 13 million securities. Financial analysts predict the collapse of the American economy.

titlelocalization.rawText: On one single evening in Detroit, 105 people died of alcohol poisoning.

descriptionlocalization.rawText: Among the deceased is the renown actor Anthony Woods. The media is blaming the management of the Boxler plant for the incident. They'd taken to mixing poison into the industrial alcohol to combat the theft of solvents. Investigators from The Bolt newspaper believe the poisoned alcohol somehow found its way into the underground bars of Los Angeles as well. Director Micheal Marsh commented on the incident to FunTimes magazine. "For the death of my friend and colleague, I ask you to blame the idiot congressmen who voted for Prohibition. I'd like to hear what they say when something like this happens to their children."
